results.name: Black White
results.title: Vans Knu Skool Black White
results.description: The Vans Knu Skool Black White is a classic skate shoe that combines style and functionality. The upper is made of durable suede and its black and white colorway is timeless and versatile, making it easy to pair with any outfit. The shoe features a padded collar and tongue for added support and comfort, while the signature rubber waffle outsole provides excellent grip and traction on the board. Released on February 18, 2023, the Vans Knu Skool Black White is priced at $75, making it an affordable option for those looking for a reliable skate shoe. The shoe is available in a range of sizes, ensuring a comfortable fit for everyone. Something we love about Vans Knu Skool Black White is its classic design that never goes out of style. Our experts think the best features of this shoe are its durable canvas upper, padded collar and tongue, and signature rubber waffle outsole. The standout feature of the Vans Knu Skool Black White is its timeless black and white colorway that can be dressed up or down. Our experts especially love the affordable price point, making it accessible to a wide range of consumers.

results.name: Checkerboard
results.title: Vans Slip-On Checkerboard
results.description:
In the late 1970s, Steve Van Doren, son of Vans founder Paul Van Doren, noticed that skateboarders in Southern California started to customize their Vans by coloring checkerboard style patterns on the shoes midsole. With this inspiration, the Vans Slip On Checkerboard was created.

The Vans Slip On Checkerboard is a cultural icon. First introduced to a global audience through an unforgettable cameo on Sean Penn's slacker character Jeff Spiccoli in the 1982 film Fast Times at Ridgemont High, the checkered Vans Slip On is a monument in the Vans line and a street staple. It features a canvas, black and white checkerboard patterned upper with a branded Vans tab. At the base, a white and gum waffle cup sole with a red heel patch completes the design.

This 2019 iteration of the Vans Slip On Checkerboard retailed for $65.

results.name: Triple Black
results.title: Vans Old Skool Triple Black
results.description: The Vans Old Skool Triple Black is a classic sneaker that has been updated with a sleek and modern design. The shoe features a black canvas upper with black suede overlays, giving it a monochromatic look that is both stylish and versatile. The iconic Vans side stripe is also black, adding to the shoe's understated aesthetic. Released on January 1st, 2019, the Vans Old Skool Triple Black is a must-have for any sneakerhead looking for a timeless and versatile shoe. The retail price of $70 makes it an affordable option for those looking to add a classic sneaker to their collection. The shoe is made with high-quality materials, including a durable canvas upper and a rubber sole that provides excellent traction and support. The cushioned footbed ensures all-day comfort, making it perfect for everyday wear. Something we love about the Vans Old Skool Triple Black is its ability to complement any outfit, from casual to dressy. Our experts think the best features of the shoe are its sleek design, durable materials, and comfortable fit. The standout feature of the Vans Old Skool Triple Black is its monochromatic colorway, which gives it a modern and sophisticated look. Our experts especially love how versatile the shoe is, making it a great addition to any sneaker collection.

results.name: Triple Black
results.title: Vans Knu Skool Triple Black
results.description:
The Vans Knu Skool Triple Black adds an all-black colorway to the retro Vans Knu Skool silhouette. In fact, the only pop of color is the orangish hue of the rubber waffle outsole.

The Triple Black Vans Knu Skool is a modern interpretation of the chunky skateboarding shoes from the 1990s with exaggerated proportions. Extra padding in the tongue and collar gives the sneaker a puffed-up appearance while preventing foot slippage and holding the heel down. The thick, black laces add another oversized feature and secure the front lace closure. Durable suede gives the sneaker a velvety appearance, while heel pull tabs help the wearer put on or take off the shoe.

Our experts at StockX like the 3D molded Sidestripe, which represents a heritage feature seen on some of Vansâ€™ most celebrated models. The Vans Knu Skool Triple Black was released on May 21, 2023, and sold for $75.

results.name: Bape ABC Multi-Camo
results.title: Vans LX Old Skool Bape ABC Multi-Camo
results.description:
The Vans LX Old Skool Bape ABC Multi-Camo gives the classic Vans Old Skool design a camouflage upgrade with mismatched colors on each shoe. This skateboarding sneaker is part of a collaboration between Vans and Bape â€“ A Bathing Ape, a Japanese streetwear label.

The Bape ABC Multi-Camo Vans LX Old Skoolâ€™s minimalist build serves as the perfect canvas to display the bold camo print favored by Bape. The left shoe covers the camo printâ€™s asymmetrical shapes in traditional green on the lateral side and in shades of blue on the medial side. In comparison, the right shoe displays green camo on the medial side and pink on the lateral side panel. Bapeâ€™s signature star logo shoots across the side panels and comes in a neutral white.

Our experts at StockX like the midsole, which features a shark tooth design at the front of the shoe. The Vans LX Old Skool Bape ABC Multi-Camo was released on July 27, 2024, and sold for $109.

results.name: Navy White
results.title: Vans Old Skool Navy White
results.description:
The Vans Old Skool sneaker is one of the shoes that helped put Vans on the map back in the 1970s. To celebrate this, Vans has continuously released new Old Skool colorways over the years, including the Vans Old Skool Navy White.

Like other Vans Old Skool options, this one featured a low-top design and an upper that had a mixture of suede and canvas. It also included a blend of navy blue and black along with Vans' iconic white Sidestripe. Additionally, it had everything from reinforced toe caps and padded collars to a lace-up closure and Vans' patented rubber waffle outsoles.

All of this kept this Vans Old Skool looking similar to many of the Old Skools that came before it, but that became what we loved about it so much. It stayed true to the original Vans vision by paying tribute to what has worked for the Old Skool for so many years now. The Vans Old Skool Navy White was released on January 1, 2000, and retailed for $70.

results.name: Black White
results.title: Vans Sk8-Hi Black White
results.description:
The Vans Sk8-Hi Black White is an iconic sneaker from the popular skateboarding brand Vans, featuring its classic black and white colorway, which remains timeless close to fifty years since it was first launched.

The shoe features a high-top design and is constructed with a combination of suede and canvas material with a rubber outsole. The upper has a stitched-up design across the toe box and side panels, and also incorporates the iconic white stripe that runs across the sides of the shoe - making it instantly recognizable. Other design elements on the shoe include the padded collar for added support, while branding details include the â€˜Vans Off The Wallâ€™ logo in Striking Red on the tongue and midsole - just under the heel like most shoes on the Vans line.

The Vans Sk8-Hi Black White was first released for retail on January 1, 2019 at the retail price of $65.

results.name: Navy White
results.title: Vans Knu Skool Navy White
results.description:
The Vans Knu Skool Navy White is a skate shoe that takes its design inspiration from the puffy skate style of the 90s.

This version of the Vans Knu Skool is made with a paneled suede upper in navy blue. The toe box, eyestays, and heel counter are all dark-blue suede stitched together with white thread. A lighter shade of blue makes up the sides of the shoes and runs around the top of the heel. The traditional Vans Sidestripe runs in puffy 3D white material across each side, and the extra puffy dark-blue tongue sports a Vans Off The Wall patch. The shoe sits on top of a white rubber midsole and has a heel pull tab for easy on and off.

Our favorite feature of this shoe is the white thread that stitches the panels of suede together on the upper, as it adds some contrast to the dark-blue shades. The Vans Knu Skool Navy White was released on February 18, 2023, for $75.

results.name: Bape ABC Camo Black Green
results.title: Vans LX Sk8-Mid Bape ABC Camo Black Green
results.description:
The Vans LX Sk8-Mid Bape ABC Camo Black Green is co-branded BAPE x Vans sneaker, the LX Sk8-Mid model, presenting in a black, green, and white color scheme.

The canvas ABC camo, which is a classic motif of the Bape brand, fills up the side panels. Black suede dons the toe box, forefoot, tongue and heel areas. At the top of the tongue is the same camouflage pattern sporting an embroidered red OFF THE WALL skateboard image. The iconic Vans jazz stripe is featured on the lateral left and medial right sides in white, while a white shooting star STA logo adorns the medial left and lateral right sides of the sneakers, so the pairs are not mirror images of each other. An "ape head" lace lock in silver sits at the bottom of the laces.

We think that this sneaker epitomizes how Vans and Bapejoined to produce a vibrant mid-top skater shoe that seamlessly blends the two brandsâ€™ images. The Vans LX Sk8-Mid Bape ABC Camo Black Green colorway released on July 27, 2024, with a $115 price tag.

results.name: Black White
results.title: Vans Old Skool Comfy Cush Black White
results.description:
The Vans Old Skool Comfy Cush Black White is a low top canvas and suede sneaker featuring a Black upper, accented by the signature Vans Sidestripe in White. White stitching and White laces further contrast the Black upper. The White sole is outlined in Black, and a red Vans Off the Wall logo tab adorns the rear heel.

American skateboarding shoe and lifestyle brand Vans began in 1966, and they have been known for their sponsorship of skate, surfing, and BMX events, as well as their involvement in cultural phenomena like the 90s Warped Tour. With the Old Skool Comfy Cush, Vans retains the iconic styling of the Old Skool silhouette, while improving its comfort with cloud-like cushioning.

In our opinion, the best feature of the Old Skool Comfy Cush is its Black and White color story, which adheres to the classic Vans aesthetic. The Vans Old Skool Comfy Cush Black White retailed at $65 upon release.

results.name: Primary Check
results.title: Vans Old Skool Primary Check
results.description: The Vans Old Skool Primary Check is a classic skate shoe that features a black and white checkered pattern on the side panels. The upper is made of durable canvas material, while the iconic Vans stripe is made of leather. The shoe also features a padded collar for added comfort and support, as well as a rubber waffle outsole for superior grip. Released in 2017, the Vans Old Skool Primary Check retailed for $75. It is available in both men's and women's sizes. Something we love about the Vans Old Skool Primary Check is its timeless design that has remained popular for decades. Our experts think the standout feature of this shoe is its durable construction, making it a reliable choice for skating or everyday wear. Additionally, the black and white checkered pattern adds a touch of personality to any outfit. Overall, we love the Vans Old Skool Primary Check for its combination of style and functionality.

results.name: Black White
results.title: Vans Authentic Black White
results.description:
The Vans Authentic Black White is a classic skate shoe that gained popularity after its release in the 1960s and has been a staple of the brand ever since.

This version of the Vans Authentic is a low-top silhouette and is made with a simple black canvas upper. This sturdy yet breathable material is often used in the production of summer footwear. White stitching attaches the different panels of canvas to each other and can be seen around the forefoot and heel. A small white Vans tag can be seen on the lateral side above the stitching. White metal eyelets secure the laces. A thick white rubber midsole rounds out the design, and a red Vans Off The Wall patch is found on the heel of the midsole. A waffle pattern appears on the sole for traction.

What we like best about this sneaker is the red Vans patch on the heel, which adds a pop of color to the otherwise black and white shoe. The Vans Authentic Black White was released on January 1, 2018, for $60.

results.name: True White
results.title: Vans Authentic True White
results.description: The Vans Authentic True White is a classic sneaker that has been a staple in the skateboarding community for decades. Made with a durable canvas upper and a vulcanized rubber sole, this shoe is built to withstand the wear and tear of daily use. The all-white colorway gives it a clean and timeless look that pairs well with any outfit. Originally released in 1966, the Vans Authentic has remained a popular choice for skaters and sneaker enthusiasts alike. The 2019 release of the True White colorway is a testament to the enduring appeal of this iconic shoe. Retailing at $60, the Vans Authentic True White is a must-have for anyone looking for a versatile and reliable sneaker.

results.name: True White (2019)
results.title: Vans Old Skool True White (2019)
results.description:
The Vans Old Skool True White (2019) is a classic skate shoe by Vans made with the Old Skool Canvas and with the classic Sidestripe low-top silhouette.

The True White (2019) Vans Old Skool boasts a robust yet lightweight construction, featuring durable canvas and synthetic uppers in a clean True White color scheme. The design incorporates a monochromatic aesthetic, combining canvas with contrasting suede panels for added visual appeal. Reinforced toecaps ensure longevity and resilience to frequent wear, while a secure lace-up closure enhances the fit. These shoes prioritize comfort, with a padded tongue, supportive collar, and cushioned lining providing superior support and flexibility. The chunky midsole delivers cushioning, and Vans' signature rubber Waffle outsoles ensure optimal traction on various surfaces.

One thing that stands out about the low-top Vans Old Skool True White (2019) is that it was the first design to showcase the famous Vans Sidestripe. The sneaker was released on the 1st of January 2019 and sold for $70.

The upper is made of premium suede and canvas materials in a bold black and white colorway, with Gallery Dept's signature paint splatter detailing throughout. This shoe is a must-have for fans of both Vans and Gallery Dept, as it seamlessly blends the two brands' aesthetics into one eye-catching design. This shoe is a true collector's item and a statement piece for any sneakerhead's collection.
